Supreme Court — Appellate Term, December, 1901.

Before McAdam. P. J.. MacLean and Scott. JJ.

E'mer A. Darling, as executor, etc., of Alfred B. Darling, Landlord-Respondent, v. John Lackner, sued as John Lockner, Tenant-Appellant. Appeal by the tenant from a juagment(in favor of the landlord and dismissing the counterclaim, rendered in the Municipal Court of the city of New York, eighth d’strict, borough of Manhattan. Samuel W. Bower (Thomas A. Atchison, of counsel), for appellant; Justin S. Galland, for respondent.

Affirmed under Wulff v. Cilemo, 26 Misc. Rep. 551, with costs. No opinion.
